         <OBJECT_CONTRACT ITEM="1">
            <TITLE>
               <P>Replacement HR and Payroll Solution</P>
            </TITLE>
            <REFERENCE_NUMBER>P0033/2017</REFERENCE_NUMBER>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="48450000"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="SERVICES"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>Adur District Council and Worthing Borough Council are seeking a replacement integrated HR and Payroll solution. The solution may be a locally hosted or a cloud based solution, but must be an established system that has delivered tangible and demonstrable benefits to other clients. Further information about the solution functionality required by the Councils can be found below.</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
            <NO_LOT_DIVISION/>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1">
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="UKJ27"/>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>Adur District Council and Worthing Borough Council are seeking a replacement integrated HR and Payroll solution. The solution may be a locally hosted or a cloud based solution, but must be an established system that has delivered tangible and demonstrable benefits to other clients. The solution should have the following functionality:</P>
                  <P>1) capable of running multiple payrolls with different paydates and payscales;</P>
                  <P>2) capable of handling a minimum 2200 multiposts;</P>
                  <P>3) capable of handling pension deductions;</P>
                  <P>4) solution must be HMRC accredited;</P>
                  <P>5) self service function for staff;</P>
                  <P>6) have a flexible customer generated reporting tool;</P>
                  <P>7) have workflow management;</P>
                  <P>8) be capable of integrating with other Council systems including Matsoft application.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
            <DATE_PUBLICATION_NOTICE>2018-04-04</DATE_PUBLICATION_NOTICE>
         </OBJECT_CONTRACT>
         <PROCEDURE>
            <CONTRACT_COVERED_GPA/>
         </PROCEDURE>
         <COMPLEMENTARY_INFO>
            <INFO_ADD>
               <P>The Councils intend to undertake market engagement exercise with a selection of potential providers to understand more about how the marketplace is developing and the type and functionality of the potential solutions available. Interested organisations should submit brief information (max two sides A4) about their organisation and an overview of the key functionality of the potential solution(s) available to the Councils to e: procurement@adur-worthing.gov.uk by 29.1.2018. It is anticipated that the market engagement exercise will take place week 6.2.2018.</P>
            </INFO_ADD>
            <DATE_DISPATCH_NOTICE>2018-01-09</DATE_DISPATCH_NOTICE>
         </COMPLEMENTARY_INFO>
      </F01_2014>
